<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="364" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.24112 RP/11–946: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Flack</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-15T19:00:00-05:00">November 15, 1946—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>613. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 1052, Nov. 9. New <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> int[erest] replacement program
                            gratifying. List <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> spearheads being
                            reviewed for possible elimination less serious cases. Dept would
                            appreciate <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> re firms <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> wish to drop so that it may comment
                            before final action. Dept also studying <pb facs="0434" n="416" xml:id="pg_416"/> Peru decree Sept 3 for effect similar <gloss target="#t_Bol1">Bol</gloss> decree would have on expropriation
                            spearheads and on Eisner and Kyllmann transfers. Your comments on latter
                            point are requested. Dept will discuss fully on recpt text draft
                            decree.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>